Steam servers are currently down, leaving PC users unable to access the network, connect with friends and play games online. The Steam server status makes grim reading for fans, who have complained about not being able to access the network. Independent website Down Detector has received thousands of reports that Steam isn't working. Carry on reading for more about the Steam outage, and for news on when the platform will be back online. The outage tracker monitors social mentions around certain topics to detect when services go down across the world. The Down Detector outage map shows that the Steam issues are mainly affecting users in the US, although there are still some reports in the UK and Europe. At the time of writing, the reports are past the 8,000 mark, making it one of the bigger Steam outages in recent memory. More to follow...